description:
Portugal's Nature Parks - Episode 1: Peneda-GerÃªs National Park | Wildlife Documentary

Watch 'Portugal's Nature Parks - Episode 2' here: https://youtu.be/OKIEm0SRXKw

In this episode:
The Parque Nacional Peneda-GerÃªs is the only national park in Portugal. An area of almost 700 square kilometers, located in the extreme north of Portugal. Barren and rocky ridges in the plateaus, contrast with large forests and lush ground vegetation in deep valleys, crossed by lakes and rivers. The park is known for its oak forests, which are predominantly pedunculate and Pyrenean oaks. Among the typical animals of the park are the small Garrano ponies, an old breed of horse and the only one in Europe still living in the wild.

Portugal, the narrow country in southwestern Europe is becoming increasingly popular with tourists. Beyond the 600 kilometers of coastline promising a beach vacation, Portugal has 
pristine, unspoiled landscapes, rare animals and plant species, and unique ecosystems.  
The series explores five of the most important nature and national parks in Portugal.
